# Docebo Authentication & SSO — HCP Portal

## Authentication Architecture

The HCP Portal (TYPO3) acts as the **Identity Provider (IdP)** — it owns HCP credentials and
sessions. Docebo is the **Service Provider (SP)** — it provides learning content and APIs.
The portal backend handles all token exchange; the frontend never sees Docebo credentials.

```
HCP Browser  ←→  TYPO3 Portal (PHP)  ←→  Docebo OAuth2 Endpoint
                   ↑ IdP                    ↑ SP
                   Owns HCP session         Provides learning APIs
                   Signs JWT tokens         Validates & returns access_token
```

## OAuth2 Endpoint

```
POST https://merzaestheticsexchangesandbox.docebosaas.com/oauth2/token
Content-Type: application/x-www-form-urlencoded
```

## Three Grant Types Compared

| Grant Type | Best For | Security | Complexity |
|---|---|---|---|
| **JWT Bearer** (RS256) | Production SSO, embedded learning | Highest (no secret transmitted) | Medium |
| **Client Credentials** | Server-to-server admin tasks | Medium (secret stays server-side) | Low |
| **Resource Owner Password** | Legacy/simple setups | Lower (credentials transmitted) | Low |

**Recommendation**: Use **JWT Bearer** for embedded learning token provisioning (user-context tokens)
and **Client Credentials** for backend admin/sync operations (service-context tokens).

## Grant Type 1: JWT Bearer (Recommended for SSO)

### Setup Requirements

1. Generate an RSA key pair (RS256):
   ```bash
   # Generate private key (keep secure, NEVER commit to repo)
   openssl genrsa -out docebo_private.pem 2048
   # Extract public key
   openssl rsa -in docebo_private.pem -pubout -out docebo_public.pem
   ```

2. In Docebo: Admin → Settings → API and SSO app → Add OAuth2 client → JWT Bearer grant
3. Upload `docebo_public.pem` to the Docebo OAuth2 client configuration
4. Note the `client_id` (you do NOT get a client_secret for JWT Bearer)

### PHP Implementation

```php
<?php
// EXT:hcp_portal/Classes/Service/DoceboJwtTokenService.php

namespace Merz\HcpPortal\Service;

use Firebase\JWT\JWT;

class DoceboJwtTokenService implements DoceboTokenService
{
    private string $clientId;
    private string $privateKeyPath;
    private string $doceboDomain = 'merzaestheticsexchange.docebosaas.com';

    private ?string $cachedToken = null;
    private ?int $tokenExpiry = null;

    public function __construct(string $clientId, string $privateKeyPath)
    {
        $this->clientId = $clientId;
        $this->privateKeyPath = $privateKeyPath;
    }

    /**
     * Get a user-context access token for embedded learning.
     * The token inherits the permissions of the specified user.
     *
     * @param string $userEmail Docebo username (email) of the HCP
     * @return string Docebo access_token
     */
    public function getUserToken(string $userEmail): string
    {
        $jwt = $this->buildJwt($userEmail);
        return $this->exchangeJwtForToken($jwt);
    }

    /**
     * Get a service-context access token (Superadmin).
     * Use for backend admin operations (user sync, enrollment, reporting).
     *
     * @return string Docebo access_token
     */
    public function getServiceToken(): string
    {
        // Check cache
        if ($this->cachedToken && $this->tokenExpiry > time() + 60) {
            return $this->cachedToken;
        }

        // Use a dedicated Docebo service account (Superadmin)
        $jwt = $this->buildJwt($this->getServiceAccountEmail());
        $token = $this->exchangeJwtForToken($jwt);

        $this->cachedToken = $token;
        $this->tokenExpiry = time() + 3600; // Default expiry

        return $token;
    }

    public function isExpired(): bool
    {
        return !$this->tokenExpiry || $this->tokenExpiry <= time() + 60;
    }

    private function buildJwt(string $subject): string
    {
        $now = time();
        $payload = [
            'iss' => $this->clientId,
            'sub' => $subject,      // Docebo username (usually email)
            'aud' => $this->doceboDomain,
            'iat' => $now,
            'exp' => $now + 300     // Short-lived JWT (5 min), not the access_token
        ];

        $privateKey = file_get_contents($this->privateKeyPath);
        return JWT::encode($payload, $privateKey, 'RS256');
    }

    private function exchangeJwtForToken(string $jwt): string
    {
        $ch = curl_init('https://' . $this->doceboDomain . '/oauth2/token');
        curl_setopt_array($ch, [
            CURLOPT_POST => true,
            CURLOPT_RETURNTRANSFER => true,
            CURLOPT_HTTPHEADER => ['Content-Type: application/x-www-form-urlencoded'],
            CURLOPT_POSTFIELDS => http_build_query([
                'grant_type' => 'urn:ietf:params:oauth:grant-type:jwt-bearer',
                'scope' => 'api',
                'assertion' => $jwt
            ]),
            CURLOPT_TIMEOUT => 10,
        ]);

        $response = curl_exec($ch);
        $httpCode = curl_getinfo($ch, CURLINFO_HTTP_CODE);
        curl_close($ch);

        if ($httpCode !== 200) {
            throw new DoceboAuthException(
                'JWT token exchange failed: HTTP ' . $httpCode . ' — ' . $response
            );
        }

        $data = json_decode($response, true);
        return $data['access_token'];
    }

    private function getServiceAccountEmail(): string
    {
        // Dedicated Docebo Superadmin account for API operations
        // Configure via TYPO3 extension settings or environment variable
        return getenv('DOCEBO_SERVICE_ACCOUNT') ?: 'hcp-portal-service@merz.com';
    }
}
```

### JWT Payload Reference

| Claim | Required | Description |
|---|---|---|
| `iss` | Yes | OAuth2 client_id from Docebo |
| `sub` | Yes | Docebo username of the user (usually email) |
| `aud` | Yes | Docebo platform domain (without https://) |
| `iat` | Yes | Issued at (Unix timestamp) |
| `exp` | Yes | Expiry (Unix timestamp, keep short: 5 min) |

## Grant Type 2: Client Credentials (Server-to-Server)

Best for backend cron jobs, data sync, reporting extraction — no user context needed.

```php
<?php
class DoceboClientCredentialsService
{
    public function getToken(): string
    {
        $ch = curl_init('https://merzaestheticsexchangesandbox.docebosaas.com/oauth2/token');
        curl_setopt_array($ch, [
            CURLOPT_POST => true,
            CURLOPT_RETURNTRANSFER => true,
            CURLOPT_POSTFIELDS => http_build_query([
                'client_id' => getenv('DOCEBO_CLIENT_ID'),
                'client_secret' => getenv('DOCEBO_CLIENT_SECRET'),
                'grant_type' => 'client_credentials',
                'scope' => 'api'
            ])
        ]);

        $result = json_decode(curl_exec($ch), true);
        curl_close($ch);

        return $result['access_token'];
    }
}
```

**Note**: Client Credentials tokens operate at the application level, not user level.
Permissions depend on the OAuth2 app configuration in Docebo.

## Grant Type 3: Resource Owner Password

Use only for legacy/testing scenarios.

```php
$ch = curl_init('https://merzaestheticsexchangesandbox.docebosaas.com/oauth2/token');
curl_setopt_array($ch, [
    CURLOPT_POST => true,
    CURLOPT_RETURNTRANSFER => true,
    CURLOPT_POSTFIELDS => http_build_query([
        'client_id' => getenv('DOCEBO_CLIENT_ID'),
        'client_secret' => getenv('DOCEBO_CLIENT_SECRET'),
        'grant_type' => 'password',
        'username' => $userEmail,
        'password' => $userPassword,
        'scope' => 'api'
    ])
]);
```

## Token Lifecycle

- **Access token TTL**: Configurable, default ~3600 seconds (1 hour)
- **Refresh token TTL**: 14 days
- **Refresh flow**: Use the refresh_token from the initial response

```php
// Refresh an expired token
$ch = curl_init('https://merzaestheticsexchangesandbox.docebosaas.com/oauth2/token');
curl_setopt_array($ch, [
    CURLOPT_POST => true,
    CURLOPT_RETURNTRANSFER => true,
    CURLOPT_POSTFIELDS => http_build_query([
        'grant_type' => 'refresh_token',
        'refresh_token' => $storedRefreshToken,
        'client_id' => getenv('DOCEBO_CLIENT_ID')
    ])
]);
```

## SSO Deep-Link URL

To redirect an HCP from the portal directly into Docebo with automatic login:

```
https://merzaestheticsexchangesandbox.docebosaas.com/learn;type=oauth2_response;access_token={TOKEN};expires_in=4000;token_type=bearer;scope=api
```

This is useful for fallback scenarios where embedded learning is not available
(e.g., complex ILT sessions, admin-level course management).

## Automatic User Provisioning Flow

When an HCP logs into the portal for the first time, the backend should
auto-provision them in Docebo before generating an embedded learning token.

```php
<?php
class DoceboUserProvisioningService
{
    private DoceboApiClient $api;
    private DoceboJwtTokenService $tokenService;

    /**
     * Ensure HCP exists in Docebo. Create if new, update if changed.
     * Called during portal login or first access to learning content.
     *
     * @param HcpUser $hcp  Portal user object
     * @param int $branchId Docebo branch ID for the HCP's cluster
     * @return int Docebo user ID
     */
    public function provisionUser(HcpUser $hcp, int $branchId): int
    {
        // Step 1: Check if user exists in Docebo
        $existing = $this->findDoceboUser($hcp->getEmail());

        if ($existing) {
            // Step 2a: Update if attributes changed
            $this->syncUserAttributes($existing['user_id'], $hcp, $branchId);
            return $existing['user_id'];
        }

        // Step 2b: Create new user
        $result = $this->api->request('POST', '/manage/v1/user', [
            'userid' => $hcp->getEmail(),
            'email' => $hcp->getEmail(),
            'password' => bin2hex(random_bytes(16)), // Random, user never types it
            'firstname' => $hcp->getFirstName(),
            'lastname' => $hcp->getLastName(),
            'role' => 'learner',
            'branch_id' => $branchId,
            'language' => $this->mapPortalLanguageToDocebo($hcp->getLanguage()),
            'valid' => true,
            // Map custom fields (e.g., specialty, clinic name)
            'field_1' => $hcp->getSpecialty(),
            'field_2' => $hcp->getClinicName(),
        ]);

        return $result['data']['user_id'];
    }

    /**
     * Deprovisioning: deactivate (don't delete) to preserve training records.
     */
    public function deprovisionUser(string $email): void
    {
        $user = $this->findDoceboUser($email);
        if ($user) {
            $this->api->request('PUT', '/manage/v1/user/' . $user['user_id'], [
                'valid' => false
            ]);
        }
    }

    private function findDoceboUser(string $email): ?array
    {
        $result = $this->api->request('GET', '/manage/v1/user', [
            'search_text' => $email,
            'page_size' => 1
        ]);

        $items = $result['data']['items'] ?? [];
        return !empty($items) ? $items[0] : null;
    }

    private function syncUserAttributes(int $userId, HcpUser $hcp, int $branchId): void
    {
        $this->api->request('PUT', '/manage/v1/user/' . $userId, [
            'firstname' => $hcp->getFirstName(),
            'lastname' => $hcp->getLastName(),
            'branch_id' => $branchId,
            'language' => $this->mapPortalLanguageToDocebo($hcp->getLanguage()),
            'valid' => true, // Re-activate if previously deactivated
            'field_1' => $hcp->getSpecialty(),
        ]);
    }

    private function mapPortalLanguageToDocebo(string $portalLang): string
    {
        $map = [
            'es' => 'spanish',   'de' => 'german',    'fr' => 'french',
            'it' => 'italian',   'pt' => 'portuguese', 'en' => 'english',
            'nl' => 'dutch',     'ru' => 'russian',    'ar' => 'arabic',
            'tr' => 'turkish',
        ];
        return $map[$portalLang] ?? 'english';
    }
}
```

## TYPO3 Extension Configuration

```php
// EXT:hcp_portal/ext_conf_template.txt (or ext_localconf.php settings)
// Store sensitive values in environment variables, NOT in TYPO3 settings

// Required environment variables:
// DOCEBO_CLIENT_ID        — OAuth2 client ID from Docebo API & SSO app
// DOCEBO_CLIENT_SECRET    — Only for Client Credentials grant (NOT for JWT)
// DOCEBO_PRIVATE_KEY_PATH — Absolute path to RS256 private key PEM file
// DOCEBO_SERVICE_ACCOUNT  — Email of the Docebo Superadmin service account
```

## Critical Security Rules

- **Private key**: Store outside web root, readable only by PHP process. NEVER commit to git.
- **Client secret**: Store as environment variable or TYPO3 encrypted configuration. NEVER in code.
- **JWT tokens are short-lived** (5 min) — they're only used to obtain the access_token
- **Access tokens**: Cache server-side with TTL slightly less than `expires_in`
- **Deprovisioning**: Deactivate users (`valid: false`) rather than deleting to preserve learning records
- **The `sub` claim in JWT must match an existing Docebo username** — provision the user BEFORE generating their embedded learning token
- **Permissions are role-based**: A token for a `learner` user cannot perform admin operations even if the OAuth2 app has broad permissions

## Debugging Auth Issues

| Symptom | Likely Cause | Fix |
|---|---|---|
| 401 Unauthorized | Token expired or malformed | Check token TTL; regenerate |
| 403 Forbidden | User role lacks permission | Check Docebo user role; use Superadmin for admin ops |
| `invalid_grant` | JWT `sub` user doesn't exist in Docebo | Provision user first |
| `invalid_client` | Wrong client_id or public key mismatch | Verify Docebo OAuth2 app config |
| Token works in API browser but not in code | Different user context (API browser uses your login) | Ensure code uses correct grant type |

